                                         JOHANNESBURG - Business Leadership South Africa has appointed Busisiwe Mavusa as its chief operations officer. She was managing director of the Black Management Forum, having been with that organisation for about eight years. In a short statement, BLSA CEO Bonang Mogale says Mavusa joins the group as a passionate activist and defender of democracy.